-MbrOXXFFJkXqA0f1idT.text: Incident reported at 3335 Emerson Ave N.

nib.text:
Two men were hospitalized after a fire broke out at a home in McKinley Thursday afternoon, officials said.

At around 2:30 p.m., firefighters responded to a report of a house fire in the 3300 block of Emerson Avenue north. 

Upon arrival, crews discovered heavy flames coming from a home and began searching for anyone inside.

Firefighters evacuated two men who had been burned and began administering medical care.

Medics transported the men to area hospitals, their conditions have not been reported. 

Shortly after, firefighters quickly extinguished the exterior of the home and began moving inside to put out the interior. 

A second alarm was called due to the excessive heat, requesting additional units and equipment. 

By 2:45 p.m., the MFD reported the bulk of the fire had been extinguished and that crews were continuing to search for any other fires that were spreading.
